## State Management
✅ Good:
```tsx
import { create } from 'zustand';

interface AuthStore {
  user: User | null;
  setUser: (user: User | null) => void;
  logout: () => void;
}

export const useAuthStore = create<AuthStore>((set) => ({
  user: null,
  setUser: (user) => set({ user }),
  logout: () => set({ user: null }),
}));
```

## Testing
✅ Good:
```tsx
import { render, screen, fireEvent } from '@testing-library/react';
import { Button } from './Button';

describe('Button', () => {
  it('calls onClick when clicked', () => {
    const handleClick = jest.fn();
    render(<Button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</Button>);
    
    fireEvent.click(screen.getByText('Click me'));
    expect(handleClick).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
  });

  it('is disabled when disabled prop is true', () => {
    render(<Button onClick={() => {}} disabled>Click me</Button>);
    expect(screen.getByText('Click me')).toBeDisabled();
  });
});
```

## Best Practices
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use React.memo for performance optimization
- Implement proper form validation
- Use proper loading states
- Implement proper error handling
- Use proper routing strategies
- Implement proper authentication flow
- Use environment variables
- Follow component composition patterns

## Common Mistakes to Avoid
- ❌ Using any type in TypeScript
- ❌ Not handling loading/error states
- ❌ Prop drilling (use context or state management)
- ❌ Not memoizing expensive computations
- ❌ Not handling side effects properly
- ❌ Not implementing proper form validation
- ❌ Not using proper key props in lists
- ❌ Not implementing proper error boundaries

## Performance Best Practices
- Use React.memo for pure components
- Implement proper code splitting
- Use lazy loading for routes
- Optimize images and assets
- Use proper caching strategies
- Implement proper bundle optimization
- Use proper development tools
- Monitor performance metrics

## Security Best Practices
- Sanitize user input
- Use proper authentication
- Implement proper CSRF protection
- Use HTTPS
- Implement proper XSS protection
- Use proper session management
- Implement proper access control
- Use secure dependencies